1
00:00:00,260 --> 00:01:33,040
♪

2
00:01:35,230 --> 00:01:40,060
♪

3
00:01:40,060 --> 00:01:41,160
I'll tell you what, Kenshin,

4
00:01:41,160 --> 00:01:44,200
I'll let you borrow my
favorite blue ribbon,

5
00:01:44,200 --> 00:01:47,170
but I'm only loaning
it to you, understand?

6
00:01:47,170 --> 00:01:49,130
I don't want you
damaging it in any way.

7
00:01:49,130 --> 00:01:50,180
You promise?

8
00:01:50,180 --> 00:01:52,240
Oh, sure, I'll take
real good care of it!

9
00:01:52,240 --> 00:01:54,020
All right, fine.

10
00:01:55,150 --> 00:01:57,190
(grunting)

11
00:01:57,190 --> 00:01:59,190
♪

12
00:01:59,190 --> 00:02:01,230
(laughing)

13
00:02:01,230 --> 00:02:03,030
Kori!

14
00:02:03,030 --> 00:02:05,040
Worried about your girlfriend?

15
00:02:05,040 --> 00:02:06,070
Don't leave!

16
00:02:06,070 --> 00:02:07,250
That's it, boy, get mad!

17
00:02:07,250 --> 00:02:10,120
Let me see you become
what you were years ago!

18
00:02:10,120 --> 00:02:12,000
Hate me with all your guts!

19
00:02:12,000 --> 00:02:15,230
Hate me enough to go back to
being Battousai the Slasher!

20
00:02:15,230 --> 00:02:17,230
Kenshin!

21
00:02:17,230 --> 00:02:20,030
(laughing)

22
00:02:20,030 --> 00:02:24,280
Jinei!

23
00:02:24,280 --> 00:02:34,240
♪

24
00:02:34,240 --> 00:02:37,010
(bird squawking)

25
00:02:39,170 --> 00:02:41,290
What do you hope to
accomplish by staring at me?

26
00:02:41,290 --> 00:02:44,190
You think I'm going to
crumble into little pieces?

27
00:02:44,190 --> 00:02:45,240
You coward!

28
00:02:45,240 --> 00:02:48,240
Is this the only way you
think you can beat Kenshin?

29
00:02:48,240 --> 00:02:52,210
♪

30
00:02:52,210 --> 00:02:54,080
Don't be stupid.

31
00:02:55,160 --> 00:02:57,150
If I wanted to defeat Battousai,

32
00:02:57,150 --> 00:02:59,230
I could do it before I
finish this cigarette.

33
00:02:59,230 --> 00:03:02,120
That's how weak he's become
since he stopped fighting.

34
00:03:02,120 --> 00:03:04,190
But what kind of
challenge would that be?

35
00:03:04,190 --> 00:03:06,180
I want him at his best!

36
00:03:06,180 --> 00:03:07,250
Now he's mad.

37
00:03:07,250 --> 00:03:09,170
Keeping you hostage
will inspire him

38
00:03:09,170 --> 00:03:11,020
to become a slasher again.

39
00:03:11,020 --> 00:03:12,150
No, you're wrong!

40
00:03:12,150 --> 00:03:13,170
He's moved past that.

41
00:03:13,170 --> 00:03:15,160
He'll never go back again!

42
00:03:15,160 --> 00:03:16,240
Is that right?

43
00:03:16,240 --> 00:03:19,130
Let me tell you, the boy's
a natural born killer!

44
00:03:20,210 --> 00:03:22,270
At the end of the
Tokugawa regime,

45
00:03:22,270 --> 00:03:25,260
Battousai was the most
talented swordsman in the land.

46
00:03:25,260 --> 00:03:27,030
He was lethal.

47
00:03:37,020 --> 00:03:39,110
Back then, I was also in Kyoto.

48
00:03:39,110 --> 00:03:41,270
I was a Royalist working
for the Restoration.

49
00:03:41,270 --> 00:03:43,090
A Royalist?

50
00:03:43,090 --> 00:03:45,130
You?

51
00:03:45,130 --> 00:03:47,040
(laughing)

52
00:03:47,040 --> 00:03:50,120
♪

53
00:03:50,120 --> 00:03:52,010
You are completely
out of control.

54
00:03:52,010 --> 00:03:53,100
To preserve our honor, Jinei,

55
00:03:53,100 --> 00:03:55,010
we're going to have
to eliminate you.

56
00:03:55,010 --> 00:03:57,260
Your death will be merciful.

57
00:03:57,260 --> 00:04:00,020
(yelling)

58
00:04:00,020 --> 00:04:02,060
♪

59
00:04:02,060 --> 00:04:04,240
(grunting)

60
00:04:04,240 --> 00:04:15,150
♪

61
00:04:15,150 --> 00:04:17,170
There was only one
fighter who had the nerve

62
00:04:17,170 --> 00:04:19,130
and the skill to challenge me.

63
00:04:19,130 --> 00:04:21,240
Battousai the Slasher.

64
00:04:21,240 --> 00:04:23,040
We fought often.

65
00:04:23,040 --> 00:04:25,100
Neither of us was able
to beat the other man.

66
00:04:25,100 --> 00:04:26,190
It was bloodlust.

67
00:04:26,190 --> 00:04:28,020
That was in the past.

68
00:04:28,020 --> 00:04:30,210
He's a much different man
than the one you remember.

69
00:04:30,210 --> 00:04:32,280
He'll never go back to
being a killing machine!

70
00:04:32,280 --> 00:04:34,090
He's beyond that!

71
00:04:34,090 --> 00:04:36,160
(laughing)

72
00:04:36,160 --> 00:04:39,070
(birds cawing)

73
00:04:41,230 --> 00:04:42,180
You're kidding!

74
00:04:42,180 --> 00:04:44,290
Kori's been kidnapped?

75
00:04:44,290 --> 00:04:48,260
"Jinei has designated the place
for the final duel between us.

76
00:04:48,260 --> 00:04:52,100
If I should die, you'll be the
only ones who can help Kori,

77
00:04:52,100 --> 00:04:53,190
but be careful!

78
00:04:53,190 --> 00:04:55,230
Jinei is as deadly
as his blades."

79
00:04:55,230 --> 00:04:56,290
Huh?

80
00:04:56,290 --> 00:04:59,170
He's gone off to
save Kori by himself.

81
00:04:59,170 --> 00:05:01,030
I guess he wants
to settle the fight

82
00:05:01,030 --> 00:05:03,160
with this creep
slasher to slasher.

83
00:05:03,160 --> 00:05:05,150
That's fine except
for one thing!

84
00:05:05,150 --> 00:05:08,220
Kenshin stopped being a
slasher a long time ago!

85
00:05:08,220 --> 00:05:12,140
It won't be a fair fight.

86
00:05:12,140 --> 00:05:15,180
He knows his skills aren't
as sharp as this monster's.

87
00:05:15,180 --> 00:05:17,080
It's his damn pride.

88
00:05:17,080 --> 00:05:39,040
♪

89
00:05:40,190 --> 00:05:41,280
There's nothing to talk about!

90
00:05:41,280 --> 00:05:43,020
I'm goin' after him!

91
00:05:43,020 --> 00:05:44,070
Wait, you fool!

92
00:05:44,070 --> 00:05:46,130
Ow, I'm gonna save
Kori and Kenshin!

93
00:05:46,130 --> 00:05:48,190
I don't care what he's
done in the past, you hear?

94
00:05:48,190 --> 00:05:50,250
I don't care about
the Tokugawa regime!

95
00:05:50,250 --> 00:05:51,240
Don't try to stop me!

96
00:05:51,240 --> 00:05:54,100
I'm not trying to stop you.

97
00:05:54,100 --> 00:05:56,100
You won't be much
help without a weapon.

98
00:05:56,100 --> 00:05:57,130
Right.

99
00:05:57,130 --> 00:06:00,060
-Don't fall behind!
-We'll see who gets there first!

100
00:06:00,060 --> 00:06:03,030
♪

101
00:06:03,030 --> 00:06:05,160
(clock ticking)

102
00:06:05,160 --> 00:06:07,240
His time is just about up.

103
00:06:07,240 --> 00:06:10,130
♪

104
00:06:10,130 --> 00:06:12,130
(gasping)

105
00:06:12,130 --> 00:06:14,280
♪

106
00:06:14,280 --> 00:06:19,030
So, the last act is
finally gonna be played out.

107
00:06:19,030 --> 00:06:20,250
Kenshin!

108
00:06:22,040 --> 00:06:23,240
(gasping)

109
00:06:26,240 --> 00:06:30,000
♪

110
00:06:30,000 --> 00:06:33,190
Your eyes tell me
you're ready to fight.

111
00:06:33,190 --> 00:06:34,270
Yes, I'm ready.

112
00:06:34,270 --> 00:06:36,160
I'm ready to have my revenge.

113
00:06:36,160 --> 00:06:38,200
I'll kill you for
kidnapping Kori,

114
00:06:38,200 --> 00:06:40,150
and for humiliating me!

115
00:06:40,150 --> 00:06:42,080
That's not the Kenshin I know.

116
00:06:42,080 --> 00:06:44,070
It's like he's possessed!

117
00:07:01,210 --> 00:07:03,020
(laughing)

118
00:07:03,020 --> 00:07:07,030
I knew the warrior in
you would finally come out!

119
00:07:07,030 --> 00:07:09,030
All you need to complete
the transformation

120
00:07:09,030 --> 00:07:10,220
is a proper weapon!

121
00:07:10,220 --> 00:07:12,130
Come on, show me
the man who killed

122
00:07:12,130 --> 00:07:14,100
for the simple joy of murder!

123
00:07:14,100 --> 00:07:17,090
Shut up!

124
00:07:17,090 --> 00:07:19,050
(laughing)

125
00:07:19,050 --> 00:07:22,050
(clanking)

126
00:07:22,050 --> 00:07:33,040
♪

127
00:07:33,040 --> 00:07:35,070
(laughing)

128
00:07:37,040 --> 00:07:39,080
This is your last battle, Jinei!

129
00:07:39,080 --> 00:07:40,130
He's enraged!

130
00:07:40,130 --> 00:07:43,100
Is this was Battousai
the Slasher was like?

131
00:07:43,100 --> 00:07:45,020
You think you can agitate me!

132
00:07:45,020 --> 00:07:47,280
Forget it, I've waited
years for this face off!

133
00:07:47,280 --> 00:07:49,280
♪

134
00:07:49,280 --> 00:07:52,280
One-handed thrust!

135
00:07:52,280 --> 00:07:56,050
Next comes a straight move
followed by the side slash.

136
00:07:56,050 --> 00:07:57,120
From there the crossroad

137
00:07:57,120 --> 00:07:59,070
leading to the
cut straight down,

138
00:07:59,070 --> 00:08:01,200
then the thrust of destruction!

139
00:08:01,200 --> 00:08:04,240
♪

140
00:08:13,070 --> 00:08:15,050
(laughing)

141
00:08:15,050 --> 00:08:16,260
Kenshin!

142
00:08:16,260 --> 00:08:21,140
♪

143
00:08:22,140 --> 00:08:24,230
-Kori!
-Kenshin!

144
00:08:24,230 --> 00:08:25,270
No answer.

145
00:08:25,270 --> 00:08:27,000
Where could they be?

146
00:08:27,000 --> 00:08:28,110
We'd better find them fast

147
00:08:28,110 --> 00:08:31,230
or there'll be nothing left
but bodies to bring home.

148
00:08:31,230 --> 00:08:33,080
This won't do.

149
00:08:33,080 --> 00:08:34,190
This is not the Battousai

150
00:08:34,190 --> 00:08:37,000
I've been waiting
for all these years.

151
00:08:37,000 --> 00:08:38,210
You see, the truth is

152
00:08:38,210 --> 00:08:41,270
you don't really
want to destroy me yet.

153
00:08:41,270 --> 00:08:45,030
As long as you feel you can
defeat me without killing me,

154
00:08:45,030 --> 00:08:48,150
I can slice you up with
very little effort at all.

155
00:08:48,150 --> 00:08:50,140
It's quite a disappointment.

156
00:08:50,140 --> 00:08:53,000
Kenshin, Kenshin!

157
00:08:53,000 --> 00:08:54,230
Leave him alone, you monster!

158
00:08:54,230 --> 00:08:56,140
You're insane, you hear me?

159
00:08:56,140 --> 00:08:57,270
You're a demon!

160
00:08:57,270 --> 00:08:59,140
Leave him alone!

161
00:08:59,140 --> 00:09:01,050
(laughing)

162
00:09:01,050 --> 00:09:03,170
Apparently you need
some more motivation!

163
00:09:11,180 --> 00:09:28,040
♪

164
00:09:28,040 --> 00:09:31,130
Ken...

165
00:09:31,130 --> 00:09:33,080
shin!

166
00:09:33,080 --> 00:09:34,260
Talk to me, Kori!

167
00:09:34,260 --> 00:09:36,120
Jinei, you did something to her!

168
00:09:36,120 --> 00:09:37,210
What did you do?

169
00:09:37,210 --> 00:09:40,110
I put a real strong
crouch spell on her.

170
00:09:40,110 --> 00:09:43,170
She should be finding
it very hard to breathe.

171
00:09:43,170 --> 00:09:47,100
She'll suffocate in
about five minutes or less.

172
00:09:47,100 --> 00:09:48,150
What?

173
00:09:48,150 --> 00:09:51,020
(laughing)

174
00:09:55,020 --> 00:09:58,050
There are only two ways to
release her from the spell--

175
00:09:58,050 --> 00:10:00,250
one would be for her
to break it on her own,

176
00:10:00,250 --> 00:10:03,100
but that would take
a person of iron will.

177
00:10:03,100 --> 00:10:06,100
Someone whose powers are
much greater than mine.

178
00:10:06,100 --> 00:10:09,210
I wouldn't count on
her being that person.

179
00:10:09,210 --> 00:10:11,270
The only other way to break it

180
00:10:11,270 --> 00:10:15,090
is if I were no longer
able to maintain control.

181
00:10:15,090 --> 00:10:17,220
♪

182
00:10:17,220 --> 00:10:20,080
In other words, you're
going to have to kill me,

183
00:10:20,080 --> 00:10:22,150
or she'll die.

184
00:10:22,150 --> 00:10:25,140
♪

185
00:10:25,140 --> 00:10:27,210
Don't you get it?

186
00:10:27,210 --> 00:10:29,220
You have no choice left!

187
00:10:29,220 --> 00:10:30,190
Unless, of course,

188
00:10:30,190 --> 00:10:32,290
you're willing to
let her choke to death.

189
00:10:32,290 --> 00:10:34,270
♪

190
00:10:34,270 --> 00:10:36,100
Damn you.

191
00:10:36,100 --> 00:10:38,270
♪

192
00:10:42,070 --> 00:10:43,100
Don't you understand?

193
00:10:43,100 --> 00:10:44,220
You have no choice here!

194
00:10:44,220 --> 00:10:47,150
Unless you're willing to
let the girl choke to death.

195
00:10:47,150 --> 00:10:49,220
That's such an ugly
way for her to die!

196
00:10:49,220 --> 00:10:52,190
(laughing)

197
00:10:52,190 --> 00:10:54,030
Stop this.

198
00:10:54,030 --> 00:10:56,120
Don't bother to
beg for her life!

199
00:10:56,120 --> 00:10:58,020
The time for talk is past!

200
00:10:58,020 --> 00:11:01,140
Whatever you have to tell me
you can say with your sword.

201
00:11:08,140 --> 00:11:10,230
(yelling)

202
00:11:10,230 --> 00:11:13,000
(panting)

203
00:11:14,080 --> 00:11:16,000
(laughing)

204
00:11:16,000 --> 00:11:18,290
I never even saw you move!

205
00:11:18,290 --> 00:11:22,060
Only one man could pull off
the soaring sword maneuver,

206
00:11:22,060 --> 00:11:25,190
a master killer
resurrected from the dead!

207
00:11:25,190 --> 00:11:28,040
That's you,
Battousai the Slasher!

208
00:11:28,040 --> 00:11:29,110
Now that you've returned,

209
00:11:29,110 --> 00:11:32,040
I presume you're
ready to face me.

210
00:11:32,040 --> 00:11:33,230
The time for talk is past.

211
00:11:33,230 --> 00:11:36,070
Whatever you have to tell me
you can say with your sword.

212
00:11:36,070 --> 00:11:37,190
I'm gonna kill you.

213
00:11:37,190 --> 00:11:40,010
Ken--Ken--Kenshin!

214
00:11:40,010 --> 00:11:41,160
You're threatening me?

215
00:11:41,160 --> 00:11:43,030
Good!

216
00:11:43,030 --> 00:11:44,130
Very good!

217
00:11:44,130 --> 00:11:46,120
♪

218
00:11:46,120 --> 00:11:48,140
I've been waiting
to hear you say that!

219
00:11:48,140 --> 00:11:50,060
Now I know you're finally back!

220
00:11:51,290 --> 00:11:54,010
This will determine
who's the best,

221
00:11:54,010 --> 00:11:55,210
me or you!

222
00:11:55,210 --> 00:11:57,180
Stop, Kenshin!

223
00:11:57,180 --> 00:11:58,250
Don't do it!

224
00:11:58,250 --> 00:12:00,200
(laughing)

225
00:12:02,110 --> 00:12:05,070
The final battle
is about to begin!

226
00:12:05,070 --> 00:12:07,140
Say your prayers, Battousai!

227
00:12:07,140 --> 00:12:16,040
♪

228
00:12:16,040 --> 00:12:18,060
-Cold feet?
-No!

229
00:12:18,060 --> 00:12:20,250
I just decided it's
best to take precautions.

230
00:12:20,250 --> 00:12:23,260
When it comes down to it,
you're no ordinary opponent.

231
00:12:23,260 --> 00:12:25,160
♪

232
00:12:25,160 --> 00:12:27,140
I figure, to protect myself,

233
00:12:27,140 --> 00:12:29,160
I better create an advantage.

234
00:12:29,160 --> 00:12:32,210
Otherwise, I might
as well commit suicide.

235
00:12:32,210 --> 00:12:34,000
The crouch spell is designed

236
00:12:34,000 --> 00:12:36,030
to make a person
weak and helpless.

237
00:12:36,030 --> 00:12:40,030
I will use a reverse version
of that spell on myself!

238
00:12:40,030 --> 00:12:42,210
When I'm through, it will
release all my dormant strength

239
00:12:42,210 --> 00:12:45,130
and put me on an
equal footing with you!

240
00:12:45,130 --> 00:12:55,140
♪

241
00:12:55,140 --> 00:12:57,150
I am unbeatable!

242
00:12:57,150 --> 00:12:59,270
I am invincible!

243
00:12:59,270 --> 00:13:04,090
♪

244
00:13:04,090 --> 00:13:07,210
I am your worst nightmare!

245
00:13:07,210 --> 00:13:09,170
There's a variation
of the crouch spell

246
00:13:09,170 --> 00:13:11,230
called the demon possession.

247
00:13:11,230 --> 00:13:13,240
I haven't used it in 15 years,

248
00:13:13,240 --> 00:13:15,290
but I was able
to invoke it today.

249
00:13:15,290 --> 00:13:18,120
Allow me to
demonstrate its power!

250
00:13:18,120 --> 00:13:25,200
♪

251
00:13:25,200 --> 00:13:26,270
Yahhh!

252
00:13:26,270 --> 00:13:29,030
(clanking)

253
00:13:34,260 --> 00:13:37,230
Very impressive, but useless.

254
00:13:37,230 --> 00:13:39,220
I said I was gonna kill you,

255
00:13:39,220 --> 00:13:42,200
and that's how it'll be.

256
00:13:42,200 --> 00:13:45,270
There's no spell strong
enough to overcome my will.

257
00:13:45,270 --> 00:13:52,250
♪

258
00:13:52,250 --> 00:13:53,210
Look at him!

259
00:13:53,210 --> 00:13:56,170
He's in the killing position!

260
00:13:56,170 --> 00:13:59,090
Removing the sword allows
him to speed up the motion

261
00:13:59,090 --> 00:14:02,060
and slice his opponent to
pieces in a split second!

262
00:14:02,060 --> 00:14:05,070
It would be bad enough in the
hands of a regular assassin,

263
00:14:05,070 --> 00:14:08,040
but his speed is supernatural!

264
00:14:08,040 --> 00:14:11,250
Now, step forward
and face me man-to-man!

265
00:14:11,250 --> 00:14:13,280
I'll show you how I got my name!

266
00:14:13,280 --> 00:14:16,180
♪

267
00:14:16,180 --> 00:14:18,180
I know where he got his name.

268
00:14:18,180 --> 00:14:21,020
From the batto technique
of drawing his sword.

269
00:14:21,020 --> 00:14:23,260
It leads to death
from a single blow!

270
00:14:23,260 --> 00:14:25,240
But he has nothing
left afterwards,

271
00:14:25,240 --> 00:14:27,220
so if I can dodge
his initial attack,

272
00:14:27,220 --> 00:14:29,240
I might be able to survive.

273
00:14:29,240 --> 00:14:32,060
♪

274
00:14:32,060 --> 00:14:34,200
I can do it--I must!

