00:14:34,200 --> 00:14:36,020
His blade is curved,

276
00:14:36,020 --> 00:14:38,140
so there will be a slight
delay in withdrawing it.

277
00:14:38,140 --> 00:14:40,010
That's his weakness!

278
00:14:40,010 --> 00:14:42,140
♪

279
00:14:42,140 --> 00:14:44,260
It's all over for
you, Battousai!

280
00:14:44,260 --> 00:14:51,110
♪

281
00:14:51,110 --> 00:14:53,180
You missed with your
first lunge, now I'm--

282
00:14:53,180 --> 00:14:55,170
(grunting)

283
00:15:00,000 --> 00:15:04,060
You tricked me with
the double batto maneuver.

284
00:15:05,060 --> 00:15:07,280
(gasping)

285
00:15:07,280 --> 00:15:09,130
I used the flying sword strategy

286
00:15:09,130 --> 00:15:12,000
followed by the
Double Dragon Flash!

287
00:15:12,000 --> 00:15:13,130
I knew that my reverse blade

288
00:15:13,130 --> 00:15:17,050
didn't suit the
standard batto technique.

289
00:15:17,050 --> 00:15:19,270
So I mastered all the variations
that were ever developed,

290
00:15:19,270 --> 00:15:22,240
and that's how I
got the name Battousai.

291
00:15:22,240 --> 00:15:24,260
I cut the tendon in
your right shoulder.

292
00:15:24,260 --> 00:15:28,000
You'll never be able
to use your sword again.

293
00:15:28,000 --> 00:15:31,120
Not that it matters, because
now I'm gonna kill you!

294
00:15:31,120 --> 00:15:38,190
♪

295
00:15:38,190 --> 00:15:40,170
Kenshin!

296
00:15:40,170 --> 00:15:44,020
(wind blowing)

297
00:15:49,160 --> 00:15:51,080
What's the matter?

298
00:15:51,080 --> 00:15:53,080
Are you having second thoughts?

299
00:15:53,080 --> 00:15:56,110
This is where your weak
will defeats you, Battousai.

300
00:15:56,110 --> 00:15:59,250
In order to save the
girl, you have to kill me.

301
00:15:59,250 --> 00:16:01,240
Stop, Kenshin!

302
00:16:01,240 --> 00:16:05,260
I understand, but for
the chance to rescue Kori,

303
00:16:05,260 --> 00:16:08,140
I'll risk becoming a
slasher one more time!

304
00:16:10,170 --> 00:16:11,250
This is my victory!

305
00:16:11,250 --> 00:16:14,190
Even as I die, I will
emerge triumphant!

306
00:16:14,190 --> 00:16:16,150
You're in a corner,
Battousai, you're trapped!

307
00:16:16,150 --> 00:16:17,260
So be it.

308
00:16:23,210 --> 00:16:26,000
My sword was a deadly weapon...

309
00:16:26,000 --> 00:16:28,080
♪

310
00:16:28,080 --> 00:16:31,070
and my swordsmanship was
just a technique for killing.

311
00:16:31,070 --> 00:16:32,260
No matter how I
tried to avoid it,

312
00:16:32,260 --> 00:16:35,030
this was the truth of my life.

313
00:16:35,030 --> 00:16:36,280
♪

314
00:16:36,280 --> 00:16:38,290
But now I've learned to
turn away from the past

315
00:16:38,290 --> 00:16:42,110
because, for me, nothing
matters anymore except Kori

316
00:16:42,110 --> 00:16:44,030
and her sweet spirit.

317
00:16:44,030 --> 00:16:47,080
♪

318
00:16:47,080 --> 00:16:49,220
Kenshin!

319
00:16:49,220 --> 00:16:51,150
Kenshin.

320
00:16:51,150 --> 00:16:53,090
Kenshin!

321
00:16:53,090 --> 00:16:55,130
I love you, Kori!

322
00:16:55,130 --> 00:16:57,140
Oh, Kenshin!

323
00:16:57,140 --> 00:17:04,290
♪

324
00:17:04,290 --> 00:17:07,220
Don't let that man force
you into killing again!

325
00:17:07,220 --> 00:17:10,140
Don't go back to
committing murder!

326
00:17:10,140 --> 00:17:13,130
(grunting)

327
00:17:13,130 --> 00:17:14,240
Kori!

328
00:17:14,240 --> 00:17:17,280
♪

329
00:17:17,280 --> 00:17:19,250
Kori, talk to me!

330
00:17:19,250 --> 00:17:22,080
Tell me you're okay!

331
00:17:22,080 --> 00:17:25,020
What did you say?

332
00:17:25,020 --> 00:17:27,010
Are you able to breathe freely?

333
00:17:27,010 --> 00:17:30,180
♪

334
00:17:30,180 --> 00:17:32,100
The spell must be broken.

335
00:17:32,100 --> 00:17:34,020
I'm okay!

336
00:17:34,020 --> 00:17:35,120
You're sure?

337
00:17:35,120 --> 00:17:36,170
I'm speaking.

338
00:17:36,170 --> 00:17:38,010
That must mean something!

339
00:17:38,010 --> 00:17:40,120
I guess I overcame
the spell somehow.

340
00:17:42,100 --> 00:17:44,010
I must say, I'm impressed.

341
00:17:44,010 --> 00:17:45,040
I would never have believed

342
00:17:45,040 --> 00:17:48,170
my spell could be
broken by a woman.

343
00:17:48,170 --> 00:17:50,030
Put away your weapon, Jinei.

344
00:17:50,030 --> 00:17:51,230
You can't use your
right arm anymore.

345
00:17:51,230 --> 00:17:54,130
There's no point to
continuing this vendetta.

346
00:17:56,020 --> 00:17:58,110
You might as well turn
yourself in to the authorities.

347
00:17:58,110 --> 00:18:00,000
It's all over for you now.

348
00:18:00,000 --> 00:18:02,200
I'm the one who
decides when it's over!

349
00:18:04,090 --> 00:18:05,270
I'll never surrender!

350
00:18:05,270 --> 00:18:06,250
Not while I can--

351
00:18:06,250 --> 00:18:08,290
(grunting)

352
00:18:13,140 --> 00:18:15,070
It's the only way.

353
00:18:19,040 --> 00:18:22,050
♪

354
00:18:22,050 --> 00:18:25,260
Don't look at me with pity
in your eyes, Battousai.

355
00:18:25,260 --> 00:18:27,120
I don't want it.

356
00:18:27,120 --> 00:18:30,260
It was better when you said
you were going to kill me.

357
00:18:32,100 --> 00:18:36,090
You may not believe it, but
you'll always be a slasher.

358
00:18:36,090 --> 00:18:37,140
Take it from someone

359
00:18:37,140 --> 00:18:41,010
who knows what
bloodlust is all about.

360
00:18:41,010 --> 00:18:45,010
Slashers are slashers
until the day they die.

361
00:18:45,010 --> 00:18:48,080
They can never be anything else.

362
00:18:48,080 --> 00:18:52,060
You're a fool if you think
you can deny your true nature.

363
00:18:52,060 --> 00:18:55,280
I'll be there to greet
you at the gates of Hell.

364
00:18:55,280 --> 00:18:58,110
(laughing)

365
00:18:58,110 --> 00:19:01,060
♪

366
00:19:04,160 --> 00:19:06,010
Maybe he's right.

367
00:19:06,010 --> 00:19:09,030
Maybe I'll be a slasher
till the day I die.

368
00:19:09,030 --> 00:19:10,290
You all right?

369
00:19:10,290 --> 00:19:12,200
I guess we should
contact the police.

370
00:19:12,200 --> 00:19:13,290
Look, footprints!

371
00:19:13,290 --> 00:19:15,160
I think they could be Kenshin's!

372
00:19:15,160 --> 00:19:16,280
What--are you sure?

373
00:19:16,280 --> 00:19:17,260
Of course I'm sure!

374
00:19:17,260 --> 00:19:19,090
They lead this way!

375
00:19:19,090 --> 00:19:21,110
They're heading
right for the meadow!

376
00:19:21,110 --> 00:19:23,210
You idiot, those are cow prints!

377
00:19:23,210 --> 00:19:24,190
No, they're not!

378
00:19:24,190 --> 00:19:25,280
I know a cow's print!

379
00:19:25,280 --> 00:19:27,060
Get out of the way!

380
00:19:27,060 --> 00:19:28,270
-Ow!
-Let go of me!

381
00:19:30,060 --> 00:19:31,120
Little brat!

382
00:19:31,120 --> 00:19:33,120
Hey, blockhead, we found them!

383
00:19:33,120 --> 00:19:34,230
Don't worry about a thing, guys.

384
00:19:34,230 --> 00:19:36,120
I'm here to help save you!

385
00:19:36,120 --> 00:19:38,150
He'll have to
save himself first.

386
00:19:38,150 --> 00:19:41,040
(laughing)

387
00:19:41,040 --> 00:19:43,110
Oh.

388
00:19:43,110 --> 00:19:45,030
Rats, after all that,

389
00:19:45,030 --> 00:19:47,030
we didn't get there
in time to help!

390
00:19:47,030 --> 00:19:48,110
What a waste.

391
00:19:48,110 --> 00:19:51,090
Probably would've done
better if we'd eaten first.

392
00:19:51,090 --> 00:19:53,250
It's hard to be a hero
on an empty stomach.

393
00:19:53,250 --> 00:19:56,150
From now on, no rescues
till after lunch.

394
00:19:56,150 --> 00:19:57,280
That was quite an experience.

395
00:19:57,280 --> 00:19:59,160
Are you sure you're
all right, Kori?

396
00:19:59,160 --> 00:20:01,020
I'm fine.

397
00:20:01,020 --> 00:20:03,130
Um, Kenshin?

398
00:20:03,130 --> 00:20:06,020
Thanks a lot for
coming to save me.

399
00:20:06,020 --> 00:20:08,160
I'm not very good at
expressing gratitude.

400
00:20:08,160 --> 00:20:10,100
Listen, the truth of the matter

401
00:20:10,100 --> 00:20:12,180
is I'm the one who
should be thanking you!

402
00:20:12,180 --> 00:20:14,050
Huh?

403
00:20:14,050 --> 00:20:16,070
Kenshin, what do you mean?

404
00:20:16,070 --> 00:20:17,260
If you hadn't stopped
me when you did,

405
00:20:17,260 --> 00:20:19,110
I would've killed Jinei,

406
00:20:19,110 --> 00:20:21,140
and my past would've
caught up with me.

407
00:20:21,140 --> 00:20:25,020
I probably would've gone
back to being a slasher.

408
00:20:25,020 --> 00:20:26,170
You saved me from that.

409
00:20:26,170 --> 00:20:29,000
I'm just glad you had
the strength to stop.

410
00:20:29,000 --> 00:20:30,250
Yeah, me too!

411
00:20:30,250 --> 00:20:32,080
Oh, I almost forgot!

412
00:20:32,080 --> 00:20:33,220
I'm still carrying
your blue ribbon!

413
00:20:33,220 --> 00:20:35,270
I wanted to be sure
to return it to you.

414
00:20:35,270 --> 00:20:36,250
Here you go!

415
00:20:36,250 --> 00:20:38,230
(groaning)

416
00:20:38,230 --> 00:20:41,020
What's the matter,
don't you want it back?

417
00:20:41,020 --> 00:20:42,130
What happened to it?

418
00:20:42,130 --> 00:20:44,180
Gee, I guess it
got a little bloody.

419
00:20:44,180 --> 00:20:47,120
That ribbon was the
nicest one I ever had!

420
00:20:47,120 --> 00:20:49,140
I should've known you'd
find some way to wreck it,

421
00:20:49,140 --> 00:20:51,040
-you clumsy ox!
-I'm sorry!

422
00:20:51,040 --> 00:20:52,180
It wasn't my fault!

423
00:20:52,180 --> 00:20:54,120
Hey, you stepped on my foot!

424
00:20:54,120 --> 00:20:55,220
What wasn't his fault?

425
00:20:55,220 --> 00:20:56,120
You're a kid.

426
00:20:56,120 --> 00:20:57,200
You wouldn't understand!

427
00:20:57,200 --> 00:20:59,170
Who are you callin' a kid?

428
00:20:59,170 --> 00:21:01,220
♪

429
00:21:01,220 --> 00:21:02,280
You're wrong, Jinei.

430
00:21:02,280 --> 00:21:04,060
I may have been a slasher once,

431
00:21:04,060 --> 00:21:06,050
but I'll never go
back to that dark path,

432
00:21:06,050 --> 00:21:07,170
no matter what happens.

433
00:21:07,170 --> 00:21:17,000
♪

434
00:21:17,000 --> 00:21:19,130
I have a new road to travel now,

435
00:21:19,130 --> 00:21:20,220
and with the help of my friends,

436
00:21:20,220 --> 00:21:22,210
I'll make that
journey in sunlight,

437
00:21:22,210 --> 00:21:24,030
not in shadow.

438
00:21:24,030 --> 00:21:34,000
♪

439
00:21:35,290 --> 00:23:14,240
♪

